INSERT INTO `events` VALUES ('Arya Kills Walder Frey',6,'Riverlands','Returning to Westeros, Arya gets her revenge for the Red Wedding by first killing Lord Walder Frey’s sons, then baking them into a pie. She gets Lord Walder to eat the pie before slitting his throat'),('Battle of Bastards',6,'The North','Sansa Stark and her half-brother Jon Snow took an army of wildlings to Winterfell to reclaim it from Ramsay Bolton and the rogue House Umber. They succeeded, thanks to the timely intervention of the knights of the Vale, who came at Sansa’s behest.'),('Battle of Blackwater',2,'The Crownlands','Stannis tried to conquer King’s Landing and the Iron Throne , but Tyrion’s tactics and intervention of Lannister forces saved the day.'),('Battle of Castle Black',4,'The North','A group of wildlings, including Jon Snow’s lover Ygritte, attempt to take Castle Black at the Wall, but they lose the battle. Ygritte is killed and dies in Jon’s arms.'),('Cersei Blows up the Sept of Baelor',6,'The Crownlands','Cersei goes full Mad Queen and in one fell swoop, destroys most of her enemies. The huge explosion wiped out most of the Tyrells, including Margaery, as well as the High Sparrow.'),('Daenerys attacks the Lannister line',7,'The Reach','Dany uses Drogon to destroy the Lannister supply wagons and the Dothraki decimate at least a part of the Lannister army, but we don’t see the full aftermath of the battle, or Jaime Lannister’s fate.'),('Hardhome',5,'Beyond The Wall','Jon Travel to Hardhome to save wildlings from whitewalker, but the night king shows up and converts all the wildlings to white walkers'),('Hodor Dies',6,'Beyond The Wall','Hodor held the door to the cave of the Three-Eyed Raven so Meera and Bran could escape the White Walkers’ undead horde, dying in the process.'),('Joffrey\'s Wedding/Death',4,'The Crownlands','King Joffrey weds Margaery Tyrell, but is poisoned at the Purple Wedding feast. It’s hilarious, until Tyrion is arrested for his nephew’s murder.'),('Jon Snow\'s Murder',5,'The North','Not all of the Night’s Watch is happy with Lord Commander Snow’s decision to ally with wildlings from beyond the wall. A small group of them stab Jon to death'),('Jon Snow\'s Resurrection',6,'The North','Melisandre resurrects Jon Snow, and He gets his revenge against the mutineers by hanging them.'),('Masters of Slaver\'s Bay Invade Meereen',6,'Essos','Masters attacked Meereen. But Daenerys showed up in the nick of time with her dragons and defeated them soundly.'),('Ned Umber\'s Death',8,'The North','Lord Ned was killed after House Umber was attacked by White Walkers'),('Ned\' Execution',1,'The Crownlands','Ned had discovered that King Robert’s kids were actually fathered by Jaime, but the new king Joffrey wouldn’t have any of that talk and took Ned’s head.'),('Night King Breaches The Wall',7,'The North','Riding the dead dragon, Night King was able to  rip a hole in the Wall large enough for the army of the dead to pass through.'),('Sansa and Arya executed Little Finger',7,'The North','Once Arya and Sansa had the loyalty of the Knights of the Vale guaranteed, they laid out Littlefinger’s crimes in public, and Arya cut his throat.'),('Stannis Burns his Daughter to Death',5,'The North','In order to ensure his victory in the north and the survival of his men, Stannis sacrifices his daughter Shireen to the Lord of Light. It doesn’t work, though — much of Stannis’ army goes AWOL the next day, his wife hangs herself'),('The Expedition eyond The Wall to capture a White Walker',7,'Beyond The Wall','Jon Snow’s expedition beyond the Wall managed to capture a wight to prove the existence of the Night King to everyone in Westeros. Viserion was killed by the Night King.'),('The Night King raises Viserion as a Wight',7,'Beyond The Wall','The Night King uses his army of the dead to drag Viserion’s body out of the frozen lake into which it crashed, and then revives him as an undead wight to add to his forces.'),('The Red Wedding',3,'Riverlands','At Edmure’s wedding, the Freys and Boltons murder Robb, his wife Talisa and his mother Catelyn, along with the rest of the Stark forces who were present.');
